If you know a `JSON` payload structure you can use `Streaming API` to read data. I created 4 different methods to read given `JSON` payload:

 1. Default Gson - use `Gson` class.
 2. Gson Adapter - use `JsonReader` from Gson library.
 3. Default Jackson - use `ObjectMapper` from Jackson.
 4. Jackson streaming API - use `JsonParser` class.

To make it comparable all these methods take `JSON` payload as `String` and return `Pojo` object which represents `A` and `B` properties. Below graph represents differences: [![enter image description here][1]][1]

As you can notice, `Jackson`&#39;s `Streaming API` is the fastest way to deserialise your `JSON` payload from these 4 approaches.

